</P>
<P>
   Pay: Unspecified.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: ``Candidates must have had experience of running
a substantial public or private sector organization at senior
management level and must possess outstanding leadership change
management and intellectual abilities. An understanding of public
sector finance and accountability is desirable; more important is a
strongly felt commitment to museums and to increasing their access
and influence.''
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Research fellow in weapons of mass destruction, the
International Institute for Strategic Studies
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Explore ways to advance public policy debates concerning
weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Commensurate with experience.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: ``The applicant should have world-class
expertise on weapons of mass destruction and a proven track record
in networking with specialists, government officials and
nongovernment organizations in Western countries as well as
regional conflict zones.''
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Deputy registrar, International Criminal Tribunal for
Rwanda
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Advise the registrar on general policy issues concerning
the tribunal, particularly with regard to judicial support and
related services.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: $97,119.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: Advanced law degree, at least 10 years relevant
work experience in national or international judicial systems,
extensive experience in court administration, including cases
extending beyond national boundaries.
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Senior program manager, Afghanistan Rural
Rehabilitation Program _ Community Self-Help
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Supervise two regional and two sub-regional offices of
the program, which is financed by the United Nations Office for
Project Services. ``The overall objective is peace building through
a particular focus on improved local governance, civil society
empowerment and poverty alleviation.''
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Unspecified.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: ``Interested candidates must possess an advanced
university degree. . . . At least 10 years professional experience
in community development/community organization, of which five
years must be at the senior management level with international
experience. Knowledge of U.N. system desirable. . . . Knowledge of
Dari (Persian) and/or Pushtu would also be an asset.''
</P>
<P>
   Not every job listing seems to be reserved for a MacArthur
fellow, Nobel finalist or child prodigy. Some seem positively
entry-level, though a close examination of the job descriptions
suggests that certain intangible assets may be desirable.
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Zone manager for Rothmans International, Ivory Coast
</P>
<P>
   Duties: ``Formulate the future strategic direction of all
commercial, political and marketing activities in this region'' for
Rothmans, the maker of Dunhill cigarettes and other tobacco
products.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Unspecified but ``highly attractive.''
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: ``You are currently a general manager or ideally
an area manager in charge of more than one market. You must display
an affinity with the region and ideally have lived and worked in
Francophone Africa. Man management and control of a large marketing
budget are key requisites.''
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Penitentiary reforms specialist
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Assist legal reform in central and Eastern Europe, the
former Soviet Union and Mongolia as staff attorney for the
Constitutional and Legal Policy Institute of the Open Society
Institute, a nonprofit organization based in Budapest.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Commensurate with experience.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: Law degree or legal experience. ``Strong
managerial and diplomatic skills.``
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Assistant professor, American University of Beirut
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Various openings in finance, information technology,
accounting, marketing, management, decision sciences/statistics,
mathematical economics, econometrics, macroeconomic dynamics and
economic growth, industrial organization, applied microeconomics,
public finance, monetary economics, financial economics, economic
planning and policy.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Unspecified.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: Ph.D., teaching and research experience.
</P>
<P>
   Job title: Chief executive officer, National Roads Authority of
Malawi
</P>
<P>
   Duties: ``Shall be responsible to the board of the National
Roads Authority for the implementation of board decisions covering
the planning, implementation and monitoring of maintenance and
development of the public road network.''
</P>
<P>
   Pay: ``A suitable remuneration package.''
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: Bachelors degree and five years experience in
``a senior management position in a large organization.''
</P>
<P>
   Job titles: Survey team leader, survey area supervisor,
administration officer, database specialist, survey area officer,
survey team geographer, deputy manager, field operations officer,
advanced mission team leader, mapping specialist, field
cartographer, geographer, mine/unexploded ordnance specialist.
</P>
<P>
   Duties: Define and quantify the scope and impact of the world
land-mine problem for the Global Landmine Survey.
</P>
<P>
   Pay: Unspecified.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifications: Unspecified.
</P>
</TEXT>
