<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Jan. 3 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
David Brady at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-BUG (Los Angeles) _ When the clock strikes midnight Dec. 31,
1999, the new millennium may start like this: Computers crash,
credit cards and ATMs won't work, the city goes dark and telephones
fall silent. Emboldened by the mayhem and confusion, criminals loot
stores, burglars prowl neighborhoods, thugs take over the streets.
Fear not: If the ultimate Y2K nightmare occurs, the LAPD plans to
be ready. By Deborah Sullivan. (Will move in the ``n'' California
and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
