   Other analysts say Saddam's pursuit of a nuclear bomb was not
slowed by the attack.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is closer now to building a nuclear weapon than he was in
January 1991,'' the month the Gulf War began, said David Albright,
president of the Institute for Science and International Security
in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Albright, who served as a nuclear-weapons inspector in Iraq, is
