</P>
<P>
   No one has found that Iraqi general. So U.S. policy makers are
praying for a spontaneous revolt within the Iraqi army to rid the
world of Saddam. The hope was best expressed last week by Gen.
Anthony C. Zinni, commander of U.S. forces in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he has growing internal problems,'' Zinni said in an
interview. ``I couldn't right now measure that. We don't have
