A5377 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AUS-Y2K-TIPS-COX     01-02 0135
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUS-Y2K-TIPS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Preparing for Y2K
 &HT;    Staff report
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Computer experts recommend preparing for potential Y2K power
outages much as you would get ready for a winter storm or a
hurricane. They suggest these steps:
</P>
<P>
   _ Store a week's supply of bottled water and food.
</P>
<P>
   _ Arrange to have on hand enough cash for a week.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you require regular medication, be sure to have more than a
few days' supply.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make copies of important financial documents, such as recent
bank deposits, account balances, mortgage payments and credit card
transactions.
</P>
<P>
   _ Buy batteries for flashlights, radios and other devices.
</P>
<P>
   _ Keep blankets and coats handy in case of cold weather.
</P>
