<P>
   The New York Times will publish another in its periodic
Education Life supplements on Sunday, Jan. 3.
</P>
<P>
   Here is a list of stories from the section. The stories, with a
slug of the form BC-EDLIFE-SLUG-NYT, will carry an ``a'' general
news category.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-HOMEWORK (Undated) _ The homework wars rage on, 100 years
later. Our correspondent visits a school in Millburn, N.J., where
they do a lot of homework. He visits an inner-city program where
there isn't parental support. And looks at the debate over how
much, how young. By Michael Winerip.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-MOM (New York) _ A first-person story of a South Bronx
teacher who set up a college scholarship fund in honor of her
mother, the neighborhood babysitter, after her death. By Patricia
Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-ONLINE (Undated) _ Bruce Weber takes an online course.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-SOFTWARE (Undated) _ Review of the latest in software
education. By Josh Barbanel.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-COLLEGE-PREP (Undated) _ A father's account of a five-day
five-college tour his daughter. By Charles Strum.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-TESTS (Undated) _ Questions and answers with two eminent
scholars on taking standardized tests. By Jacques Steinberg.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-QUIZ (Undated) _ Great historical moments on campuses. By
William H. Honan.
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-CHOICE (Undated) _ Aside from academic considerations,
what makes kids pick certain colleges. By Linda Lee. (1200 words)
</P>
<P>
   EDLIFE-INTERVIEW (Undated) _ Jenny Lynn Bader, playwright and
Harvard interviewer, writes a play on the interview process.
</P>
