<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-2000-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Millennium travel possibilities
 &HT;    By Cheryl Blackerby
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Even if New Year's Eve usually means trying to keep your eyes
open until midnight so you can watch the countdown at Times Square
on TV, this year will be different.
</P>
<P>
   How many times do you get to experience the start of a new
millennium?
</P>
<P>
   But it's crucial to make plans ASAP. Space in hotels, on tours
and cruises is selling out fast.
</P>
<P>
   Here are some outlandish, lavish and a few
within-the-realm-of-possibility suggestions to ring in the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
   But beware: Most are expensive. Even modest hotels are charging
new millennium prices on the eve of the Big Day.
</P>
<P>
   1. Cruise around the world
</P>
<P>
   Yes, The World Cruise Company's Ocean Explorer I will set sail
from Athens, Greece, Nov. 19 and passengers will circumnavigate the
globe three times on the 361-day voyage. They will visit 55
countries on all seven continents. The price is $35,947 per person
based on double occupancy _ only $99.58 per day! Passengers will
have options of more than 470 shore excursions, including African
safaris. The fare includes round-trip air fare from New York to
Athens. For more information, contact The World Cruise Company at
(888) 558-0887.
</P>
<P>
   2. Have a Grand time
</P>
<P>
   There are rooms still available in Grand Canyon National Park at
Maswik Lodge (a half-mile from the park headquarters and restaurant
on the South Rim), and Yavapai Lodge (1 1/2 miles from the South
Rim). Rooms at Maswik are $112 and $72; and at Yavapai, $83 and
$98. For reservations, call (303) 297-2757.
</P>
<P>
   3. Enjoy ancient wonders
</P>
<P>
   Instead of buying that entry-level BMW, visit 10 of the world's
most famous and ancient architectural wonders such as Petra in
Jordan and Luxor Temple in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
   The Great Builders Millennium trip begins Dec. 14 in Hong Kong.
Stops include the glittering temples of Rangoon, Myanmar, along
with sites in Cambodia, India and Egypt. New Year's Eve will be
celebrated in Istanbul. The expedition costs $29,950 per person and
includes hotel accommodations, meals and group transportation.
</P>
<P>
   For reservations, call TCS Expeditions, (800) 727-7477.
</P>
<P>
   4. Celebrate in South Africa
</P>
<P>
   Travelers can celebrate the start of the new year in either Cape
Town, Kruger National Park or Sun City. Starting at $6,795 per
person, African Travel's tour packages include a variety of
accommodations, all meals while on safari, game viewing with
professional guides, and sightseeing tours. Contact African Travel
Inc. at (800) 421-8907.
</P>
<P>
   5. Make a pilgrimage to Rome
</P>
<P>
   Beneath the soaring porch of St. Peter's Basilica is the
towering bronze Holy Door. Striking the door three times with a
ceremonial hammer next Christmas Eve, Pope John Paul II will usher
in a millennial Holy Year.
</P>
<P>
   The Holy Year will end on the Feast of the Epiphany, Jan. 6,
2001, when the pope celebrates Mass and ceremonially closes the
Holy Door at St. Peter's. But before that, grand events gathering
hundreds of thousands in celebration and prayer will occur.
</P>
<P>
   6. Marry on Turtle Island
</P>
<P>
   Turtle Island resort in the Fiji Islands is able to provide the
first Wedding Ceremony in the Millennium due to its observance of
daylight savings time and convenient location on the international
date line. For $200,000, a couple will receive accommodations for
10 days in the luxury resort along with a wedding ceremony,
reception and honeymoon. The resort will donate the $200,000 to
build a medical center on the island. Contact Turtle Island at
(877) 288-7853 or your travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   7. Party in the Big Apple
</P>
<P>
   The Fitzpatrick Manhattan Hotel (687 Lexington Ave., New York,
N.Y. 10022; 212-355-0100) is offering one celebrant and 181 of his
or her closest friends the chance to take over the entire 17-story
hotel for three nights. All food, alcohol and entertainment are
included, as are a New York Harbor cruise and a New Year's Eve
extravaganza. The cost? A cool $1 million. Well, it only happens
once a century.
</P>
<P>
   8: Party at Amelia
</P>
<P>
   Amelia Island Plantation, a luxury beach resort on Florida's
northeast coast, is offering a three-night package beginning Dec.
30 or 31 that includes room, all recreation, all meals and
beverages, and a millennium party with an open bar and
entertainment by four bands. The cost is $2,000 per person. Call
(800) 874-6878.
</P>
<P>
   9: Feeling lucky? Try Vegas
</P>
<P>
   Try Vegas. But watch out _ rooms in Las Vegas, normally a great
bargain, are expensive for the big night. Rooms at the new New
York-New York Hotel usually start at $49. But to stay there New
Year's Eve you have to buy a three-night package (starting Dec. 30)
for $2,000. The ``package'' includes only the room. Call (800)
693-6763.
</P>
<P>
   10: Ski at Winter Park
</P>
<P>
   Ski at Winter Park: There's still space at the small
bed-and-breakfasts and luxury resorts in Winter Park, Colo. On New
Year's Eve, there will be fireworks and a big party at the base of
the ski slopes. Call (800) 729-5813.
</P>
<P>
   11: Sail the Queen
</P>
<P>
   The Queen Elizabeth 2 will cruise out of Miami Dec. 20 on a
15-day voyage to the Caribbean. Special activities are planned.
Fares start at $5,380 per person for an inside cabin. Contact a
travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   12: Walk into 2000
</P>
<P>
   Country Walkers is offering a walk around Maui, Hawaii, from
Dec. 27 to Jan. 2. Rooms are in oceanfront resorts and mountain
lodges. The price per person is $2,195 and includes room and meals.
Call (800) 464-9255.
</P>
<P>
   13: Visit Bethlehem
</P>
<P>
   Nearly $100 million is being spent rebuilding Manger Square,
Bethlehem's central plaza, installing dramatic new lighting along
Nativity Street, and refurbishing scores of neglected architectural
treasures. Religious and secular events are planned from the Advent
season in 1999 through Easter 2001.
</P>
<P>
   14: Put on the Ritz
</P>
<P>
   For $100,000, you get a two-night weekend in a Ritz-Carlton
Suite, the premier suite in each hotel. Couples receive 18-karat
gold watches, limousine service, butler service, daily massage for
two, and a Jaguar at their disposal. Meals and parties are
included. Contact the Ritz-Carlton at (800) 241-3333 or a travel
agent.
</P>
<P>
   15: Take a classic journey
</P>
<P>
   The travel company Classic Journeys offers four millennium
packages, to Belize, Turkey, Costa Rica or Morocco. Contact Classic
Journeys at 800-200-3887.
</P>
<P>
   16: Sail away
</P>
<P>
   The deluxe triple-masted Sea Cloud, a 360-foot sailboat, will
sail the Danube River from Munich on Dec. 27, arriving in Budapest
Jan. 4. Concerts and gala dinners will be provided on board. New
Year's Eve will be celebrated at a private palace in Vienna. Prices
range from $5,800-$12,500 and include meals on board, excursions
and sightseeing and service charges. Call (212) 486-0353.
</P>
<P>
   17: Party in the Caribbean
</P>
<P>
   The Bitter End Yacht Club in North Sound, Virgin Gorda, British
Virgin Islands (800-872-2392) has a 10-day package that includes a
millennium bash with 15 bands playing a 12-hour session on New
Year's Eve. The package includes accommodations, transfers, meals
and entertainment. The cost is $10,800 per couple.
</P>
<P>
   18: Have a veddy British New Year
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps the tranquility of the English countryside beckons? The
Lygon Arms (High Street, Broadway, WR12 7DU, England; 800-63-SAVOY)
has a three-night package that includes a helicopter tour of the
Cotswolds, a New Year's Eve ball and the services of a psychic on
New Year's Day. Accommodations and most meals are included in the
$1,411 price.
</P>
<P>
   19: Grab a piece of the Rock(ies)
</P>
<P>
   The Broadmoor (Box 1439, Colorado Springs, Colo. 80901;
800-634-7711), built in 1918, will have an all-inclusive weekend
party that includes a dinner dance and a New Year's Eve show with
Bernadette Peters and the Temptations. Horse-drawn
sleigh-and-carriage rides will be available on New Year's Day. The
cost starts at $5,000 per couple.
</P>
<P>
   20: Our vote for best millennium cruise deal
</P>
<P>
   Costa Cruises' CostaVictoria sails out of Fort Lauderdale Dec.
26 on a seven-night cruise to Key West, Playa del Cozumel, Ocho
Rios and Grand Cayman. Rates start at only $1,779 per person
including port charges. Contact a travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   Don't even think about it
</P>
<P>
   These places are all booked for New Year's Eve 1999.
</P>
<P>
   _ All of Disney World's hotels are filled. You can get on a
waiting list
</P>
<P>
   (call 407-W-DISNEY) but don't hold your breath.
</P>
<P>
   _ You won't be one of the lucky ones to see the first eruption
of Old Faithful in the new millennium at Yellowstone National Park.
The park's two hotels that are open in the winter, Mammoth Hot
Springs Hotel and Old Faithful Snow Lodge, are booked.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rooms at small inns in Key West are hard to find. The desk
clerks at the popular Westwind Inn and the Island City House, a
complex that includes the island's oldest hotel and several
historic conch houses, laugh when you ask about New Year's Eve.
(But a few inns such as La Mer, the Dewey House, and Flagler's
luxurious Casa Marina are not taking reservations until February.)
</P>
<P>
   There must be a million 2000 web sites
</P>
<P>
   Here's a sampling of Web sites listing events related to the
millennium:
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.everything2000.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.party2000.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://allonetribedrum.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.la2000.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.2000celebration.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.countdown2000.com
</P>
<P>
   _ http://www.jepa.co.uk/shopping/party.html (an international
register of millennium celebrations)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
