   (NYT11) MIDDLEBURY, Vt. -- Jan. 2,1999 -- EDLIFE-COLLEGE-PREP,
1-2 -- Allen Cowett, a senior at Middlebury College, spends most of
his time on tours walking backwards. Cowett is one of the college's
campus tour guides, the first tenuous link between campus and
prospective undergraduate. (Paul O. Boisvert/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) BALTIMORE -- Jan. 2, 1999 -- EDLIFE-HOMEWORK, 1-2 -- At
the Dr. Bernard Harris Elementary School, Denise Norfleet, a
teacher, helps thrid graders after school with their homework. In
the last 15 years, the biggest increase in homework has fallen
mainly on the youngest citizens. This generation's parents are
caught in a trap of their own making: they are pushing their
children and their schools to be more competitive, even as they
have less time to help with homework and activities. (Ann
Grillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
