<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Saturday, 1/2/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) MIDDLEBURY, Vt. -- Jan. 2,1999 -- EDLIFE-COLLEGE-PREP,
1-2 -- Allen Cowett, a senior at Middlebury College, spends most of
his time on tours walking backwards. Cowett is one of the college's
campus tour guides, the first tenuous link between campus and
prospective undergraduate. (Paul O. Boisvert/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) BALTIMORE -- Jan. 2, 1999 -- EDLIFE-HOMEWORK, 1-2 -- At
the Dr. Bernard Harris Elementary School, Denise Norfleet, a
teacher, helps thrid graders after school with their homework. In
the last 15 years, the biggest increase in homework has fallen
mainly on the youngest citizens. This generation's parents are
caught in a trap of their own making: they are pushing their
children and their schools to be more competitive, even as they
have less time to help with homework and activities. (Ann
Grillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) NEW YORK -- Jan. 2, 1999 -- EDLIFE-MOM, 1-2 -- At the
Melrose Housing Projects in the South Bronx, Patricia James Jordan,
left, talks with Letesha Reese, center, 1995's recipient of the
Juanita James scholarship, and Kanika Brooks, 1998's winner.
``Though she died more than 13 years ago, my mother is still having
an influence on the youth of the neighborhood through the
scholarship fund,'' says Ms. Jordan, who set up the college fund in
honor of her mother. (Edward Keating/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 2, 1999 -- IMPEACH-LOTT, 1-2 -- Senate
Majority Leader Trent Lott, right, has consulted with many of his
