<SLUG> BC-TWISTER03-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    WEATHER: Tornado damages homes in South Florida
 &HT;    By Alexandra Navarro Clifton
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIVIERA BEACH, Fla. _ Tracey Howard and her neighbors were
sleeping just before dawn Saturday when the windows started
rumbling. Then they shattered, letting in the wind and water that
destroyed most of her and her family's belongings.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's true what they say,'' Howard said Saturday afternoon.
``It sounded like a freight train.''
</P>
<P>
   The National Weather Service in Miami confirmed that category
F-1 tornado ripped through Howard's Riviera Beach neighborhood at
about 5 a.m. Saturday, tearing shingles off roofs, snapping
concrete electricity poles and even overturning a semi-truck.
</P>
<P>
   Tornadoes are classified between F0 and F5 on the Fujita Wind
Damage Scale. A minor F0 tornado's winds are 72 mph or less. An
extremely destructive F5 tornado's winds range between 260 and 310
mph. The tornado that hit Riviera Beach Saturday, an F1, had winds
between 73 and 112 mph.
</P>
<P>
   Riviera Beach police officials said the more severely damaged
homes, including Howard's, were on the 700 and 800 blocks of 4th
and 5th Streets, just west of the Port of Palm Beach, but said much
of the city experienced flooding and lost power.
</P>
<P>
   Stephanie Lurry, who lives next door to Howard, had a pile of
wood stacked on her kitchen floor alongside pools of water and
piles of debris.
</P>
<P>
   Away from the heat and debris inside, two of Howard's four
children played with their yet-unnamed puppy, looking down at the
street and nodding when asked whether the storm woke them.
</P>
<P>
   ``We lost everything,'' Howard said. `` There's nothing I can
do.''
</P>
<P>
   The American Red Cross provided food and water and set up a
temporary shelter at 2409 Avenue H Saturday afternoon for people
affected by the storm.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
